    <note>Lin(1) Shiyue [1167] According to Lin(1) Guangchao [10612], his family and that of Shiyue were tongjia for several generations, which may mean that they were merely close associates, but also may mean that they were intermarried since it appears that Shiyue may have been the father-in-law of Guangchao, and Shiyue's youngest daughter was the wife of Guangchao's son. This is one of the few instances of same surname marriage. XNYL, 118.3a; Guangdong TZ, 15.11b; Lin Guangchao, WJ, 9.23b-26b. CBD, 2, 1395.</note>
